cs.PL, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.DS

This paper is about a language for describing grammars, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the performance of parsers generated from these grammars, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG), software engineering (cs.SE), or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
